Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setSdpMode(25.10)                                            setSdpMode(25.10)

Name
       setSdpMode - Sets SDP-related sticky options before using commands like
       placeSdpGroup and place_design

Syntax
       setSdpMode

       [-help]

       [-clock_location {bottom|center}]

       [-disable_extended_core {true|false}]

       [-honor_dont_use {true|false}]

       [-honor_orient {true|false}]

       [-legalization {NONE|SW|SE|NW|NE|AUTO}]

       [-legalization_effort {low|medium|high}]

       [-max_move_distance <value>]

       [-num_column <numberOfCol>]

       [-place_report <file_name>]

       [-pre_fixed_cells_blockage_direction {NONE|X|Y}]

       [-reset]

       Sets  SDP-related  sticky  options before using commands like placeSdp-
       Group and place_design. You can use the setSdpMode command  to  disable
       extension  of  core  boundary before running the placeSdpGroup command.
       You can also use this command to generate a detailed SDP placement  re-
       port.

       Before setting SDP options with setSdpMode, you should have:

              * Imported the design

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each setSdpMode parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man setSdpMode.

       -clock_location {bottom | center}
              Specifies  where  the Integrated Clock Gating (ICG) cell will be
              placed in an SDP register column.

              Default: center

       -disable_extended_core {true | false}
              Disables extension of the core boundary. If you set -disable_ex-
              tended_core to true before running  the  placeSdpGroup  command,
              the  software  does  not adjust the core boundary to accommodate
              all SDP placements. Instead, the software places  the  SDP  ele-
              ments  outside  the  core boundary if they do not fit within the
              boundary.

              Default: true

       -honor_dont_use {true|false}
              Specifies whether the dont_use attribute on base cells should be
              honored by the placeSdpGroup command during EEQ swapping in  SDP
              legalization. By default, placeSdpGroup takes all cells into ac-
              count.  If -honor_dont_use is set to true, placeSdpGroup ignores
              cells with the dont_use attribute.

              Default: false

       -honor_orient {true|false}
              Honors user-specified orientation during legalization.

              User-specified orientation can be set using  the  setSdpGroupAt-
              tribute command. You can use the getSdpGroupAttribute command to
              check  the current orientation setting. Note that the SDP writer
              writes out orientation information only if its value is  defined
              by the user through the SDP file or TCL command.

              Default: false

       -legalization {NONE|SW|SE|NW|NE|AUTO}
              Specifies  the  corner  of  the  SDP box that will be kept fixed
              while legalizing an SDP instance.

              Default: NONE

       -legalization_effort {low|medium|high}
              Specifies the legalization effort in placing SDP groups.

              When you run placeSdpGroup, the SDP groups are legalized on  the
              basis  of their order, which is determined by their size. Bigger
              SDP groups are placed first, and multiple iterations are used to
              place and align the remaining SDP groups. You can  also  control
              the  legalization  effort applied by using the -legalization_ef-
              fort parameter. The higher the setting of  this  parameter,  the
              more the number of iterations attempted to try and place the SDP
              groups legally.

              Default: low

       -max_move_distance <value>
              Specifies how far an SDP can be moved from its original cluster-
              ing location to resolve overlaps. By default, this value is half
              the  perimeter  of  the core box. The Manhattan distance between
              the new and original locations of the SDP must be less than  the
              value of the -max_move_distance option.

              The -max_move_distance option is honored by the refinePlace com-
              mand.  SDP  columns start at the center-of-mass of the instances
              and then try to find a legal location without overlaps.

              Default: 0

       -num_column <numberOfCol>
              Specifies the number of flip flop columns for each SDP group.

              Default: 2

       -place_report <file_name>
              Generates a detailed SDP placement report when placeSdpGroup  is
              run.

              Default:  If setSdpMode -place_report has not been specified be-
              fore running placeSdpGroup, this report is not generated.

              Note: To disable the -place_report option once it has been spec-
              ified, specify <file_name> as a null string ("").  The  detailed
              SDP placement report will not be generated subsequently.

       -pre_fixed_cells_blockage_direction {NONE|X|Y}
              Creates  temporary  placement blockage internally over pre-fixed
              cells (that is, well tap or power switch cells) in X or Y direc-
              tion to prevent SDP cells to be placed in the horizontal or ver-
              tical empty spaces when resolving overlapping.

              The illustration below shows the difference between  SDP  place-
              ment without this setting and with -pre_fixed_cells_blockage_di-
              rection set to Y.

              Default: NONE

       -reset Resets all or specified options to default value

Examples
              * The  following command disables extension of the core boundary
                if the boundary cannot accommodate all SDP placements:

                setSdpMode -disable_extended_core true

              * The following commands place elements or instances of all  de-
                fined  SDP groups and generate a detailed SDP placement report
                named dtmf_chip.sdp.rpt:

                setSdpMode -place_report dtmf_chip.sdp.rpt

                placeSdpGroup

              * The following commands control SDP movement from its  original
                cluster location to resolve overlaps:

                setSdpMode -max_move_distance 30

                place_design -sdp

